SIMPLE: infarct
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infarct
<hw>In*farct"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Infarce</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An
obstruction or embolus in one of the blood vessels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The morbid condition of a limited
area resulting from such obstruction; also, the localized necrotic
(dead) tissue resulting from such obstruction; <as>as, a hemorrhagic
<ex>infarct</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infarction</ent>⟦br⟧
